"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-01-bbc-olympic-studio-falls-silence-clare-balding-almost-stops-broadcasting-21345718\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"TheBBCstudio at theParisOlympicsfell into silence and an emotionalClare Baldingnearly stopped broadcasting overAndy Murray's official retirement.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 116, \"end\": 122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.407224021955933e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murraylost in the quarter-finals of the men's doubleson Thursday next to Dan Evans as Taylor Fritz and Tommy Paul produced a 6-2 6-4 Roland-Garros win.\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"score\": 0.9997680773648411, \"rank\": 0.00023197643571243857, \"text\": \"Dan Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\"}, {\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taylor Fritz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\"}, {\"begin\": 250, \"end\": 260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3822836938045851e-21, \"text\": \"Tommy Paul\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Balding,who regularly workson the BBC's Wimbledon coverage, was left incredibly emotional and burst into tears as Murray's retirement was confirmed.\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9998780945746132, \"rank\": 0.00012188136413308906, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 414, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.407224021955933e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'In terms of his professional playing career, that is it,' Balding said.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It is now over and all we can say is thank you\\u2026 Thank you\\u2026 (gets emotional), you better say something!'\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 627, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Balding was then handed a box of tissues as she wiped away tears, before resuming her presenting duties, next to swimmer Rebecca Adlington in the studio.\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Adlington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebecca Adlington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Adlington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Adlington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray will surely go down as one of the best - if notthebest - Great British sportsman of all time and plans are already being made to honour his legacy.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 784, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.407224021955933e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9113297241142186, \"rank\": 0.08530718095378885, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Lawn Tennis Association (LTA) issued a statement as soon as Murray played his last professional match, announcing that a court will be named after him.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999998742624, \"rank\": 1.2562763232790906e-10, \"text\": \"Lawn Tennis Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.819619426581347e-30, \"text\": \"LTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1004, \"end\": 1010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.407224021955933e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think you better say something.\\\"\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u00adClare Balding paid an emotional tribute to Andy Murray after he played the final match of his career \\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4#Olympics#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/IkWwJoylpW  'The LTA has today paid tribute to the incredible career of Andy Murray following his retirement from professional tennis,' they said.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.714429706914175e-55, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.819619426581347e-30, \"text\": \"LTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.714429706914175e-55, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Born on May 15, 1987, Murray burst to prominence winning the 2004 US Open junior singles title and the following summer, made his Tour-level debut as a wild card entrant reaching the third round of both Queens and Wimbledon, captivating the attention of the nation, where he has firmly remained during the last two decades.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1447, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.407224021955933e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Andy set many records during arguably the most competitive era in men's tennis, including winning three Grand Slam singles titles, two Olympic Gold medals, leading his country to Davis Cup success and achieving the world No.1 ranking.\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1861, \"end\": 1865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"score\": 0.9999827482612287, \"rank\": 1.725203638629137e-05, \"text\": \"Slam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\"}, {\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davis_Cup\", \"score\": 0.9999999998901785, \"rank\": 1.0821316105098937e-10, \"text\": \"Davis Cup\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davis_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davis_Cup\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The LTA is committed to working with Andy and the Murray family to ensure that his career is suitably recognised.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1992, \"end\": 1995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.819619426581347e-30, \"text\": \"LTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2038, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.407224021955933e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As part of this the LTA have committed \\u00a35m to support Judy Murray's plans to build a tennis centre of national significance for Scotland at the Park of Keir, near Dunblane.\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.819619426581347e-30, \"text\": \"LTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2156, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Judy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2230, \"end\": 2238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8330558245657951, \"rank\": 0.19583483773306593, \"text\": \"Scotland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2265, \"end\": 2273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunblane\", \"score\": 0.9751225509403625, \"rank\": 0.02551212565516453, \"text\": \"Dunblane\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunblane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunblane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The LTA is also working with Government and other partners in ensuring Andy's achievements and his legacy will benefit future generations for years to come.\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2281, \"end\": 2284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.819619426581347e-30, \"text\": \"LTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'More immediately the LTA is today announcing that from 2025 the\\u00a0centre court seating arena at the LTA's London Championships held at The Queen's Club will be known as'The Andy Murray Arena'.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2457, \"end\": 2460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.819619426581347e-30, \"text\": \"LTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2507, \"end\": 2512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_court\", \"score\": 0.9999999999049578, \"rank\": 8.890490670451066e-11, \"text\": \"court\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_court\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennis_court\"}, {\"begin\": 2534, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.819619426581347e-30, \"text\": \"LTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lawn_Tennis_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Andy has a special relationship with the tournament, having won the event more than any other in his career, and more times than any other player in the Championships' 123-year history.\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'The new name for the arena will be used at both the WTA 500 and ATP 500 events to be held at the venue from 2025.'\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Olympics judge sent home over 'inappropriate' photo  ArrowMORE:How Andy Murray withstood seven years of 'abuse' to become Great Britain's best sportsman of all time  ArrowMORE:IOC defends decision to a allow Imane Khelif to box at th